<div class="quickstart">
  <div class="quickstart__bg">
    <div class="quickstart__container">
      {% assign time = 'now' | date: "%k" | plus: 0 %}
      {% if time >= 12 %}
      <h1>Good Afternoon!</h1>
      {% else %}
      <h1>Good Morning!</h1>
      {% endif %}

      <div class="step step--active">
        <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
        <div class="step__text">
          <h2>Create a space and a story</h2>
          <p>
            A space is a place where you keep all the content related to a single project. A story is a <strong>content entry</strong> which contains one or a collection of components.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="step__last">
          <img src="//a.storyblok.com/f/40479/7a07f54a99/space.svg">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step {% if story.content.body != blank %} step--active {% endif %}">
        <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
        <div class="step__text">
          <h2>Your first API Request</h2>
          <p>
            Storyblok is an API based CMS for Components - so it's all about your data - execute a simple GET Request to see the basic structure of the story you're actually editing here.
            {% if story.content.body == blank %}<button class="btn" data-first-api data-track="interaction: first-api">Make a Call</button>{% endif %}
          </p>
          <div id="first-api" {% if story.content.body == blank %} class="quickstart--hidden"{% endif %}>
            <h3>There you go:</h3>
            <div class="quickstart__t quickstart__t--borderless quickstart__t--active">
              <pre><code data-pretty data-skip-body="true">{{story|json}}</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p>You can do this API Request with every language you can think of - we made some <a href="https://www.storyblok.com/docs/Delivery-Api/introduction" target="_blank">example calls</a> for you.</p>
            <div class="quickstart__t quickstart__t--borderless quickstart__t--active">
              <pre><code>curl -X GET "https://api.storyblok.com/v1/cdn/stories/{{story.full_slug}}?token={{private_token}}&version=draft"</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step {% if story.content.body != blank %} step--active {% endif %}">
        <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
        <div class="step__text">
          <h2>Create your first component and define its structure</h2>
          <p>
            Let's create a <strong>teaser component</strong> <i>together</i> - press <strong>start tour</strong>.
          </p>
          <button class="btn" data-start-tour data-track="interaction: start-tour">Start tour</button>
        </div>
        <div class="step__last">
          <img src="//a.storyblok.com/f/40479/9de132979f/story.svg">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step {% if proxy_mode %}step--active{% endif %}">
        <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
        <div class="step__text">
          <h2>Good job!</h2>
          <p>You've just changed content and created your first unique content component! Let's have a look at what has changed after you've done that. <button class="btn" data-second-api data-track="interaction: second-api">Run API Call</button></p>
          <div class="quickstart--hidden" id="second-api">
            <div class="quickstart__t quickstart__t--borderless quickstart__t--active">
              <pre><code data-pretty data-skip-body="">{{story|json}}</code></pre>
            </div>
            <em>Tip: You can add more <a href="https://www.storyblok.com/docs/terminology/field-type" target="_blank">fields with different types</a> to your component and fill it with content.</em>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step {% if proxy_mode %}step--active{% endif %}">
        <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
        <div class="step__text">
          <h2>Time to show</h2>
          <p>
            For maximum flexibility, Storyblok can be integrated into your application or website retrieving content from our API. But for those who want just a basic website, we offer a <a href="https://www.storyblok.com/docs/Rendering-Service/Introduction" target="_blank">rendering service</a> where the whole website is hosted in the cloud.
          </p>
          <div>

            <button class="btn" data-api-sdk-boilerplates data-track="decision: API only">API / SDK / Boilerplates</button>
            <button class="btn" data-rendering-service data-track="decision: rendering service">Rendering Service</button>

          </div>
          <div>
            <button class="quickstart__button--link" data-show="#not-sure" data-track="decision: not-sure">I'm not sure yet</button>
            <div id="not-sure" class="quickstart--hidden">
              <table class="quickstart__table">
                <tr>
                  <th></th>
                  <th>API / SDK / Boilerplates</th>
                  <th>Rendering Service</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Templating Engine</td>
                  <td>Any</td>
                  <td>Liquid</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Custom Backend Logic</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                  <td>Predefined Liquid Filters</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Local Environment</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Dev Environment</td>
                  <td>Own</td>
                  <td>Included</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Live Environment</td>
                  <td>Own</td>
                  <td>Included</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Direct Hosting</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Custom Domain</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Storyblok Subdomain</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Included CDN</td>
                  <td>API / Images / Assets</td>
                  <td>Everything</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Pricing</td>
                  <td class="quickstart__text--center" colspan="2">included</td>
                </tr>
              </table>
              <p>You are still not sure? <button data-trigger-livechat class="quickstart__button--link">Contact us</button> - let's get through this together!</p>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="api-sdk-boilerplates">
        <h1>API / SDK / Boilerplates</h1>
        <div class="step">
        <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
        <div class="step__text step--choose-tech">
          <h2>Fetch and render the content</h2>

          <p>You can choose the Storyblok hosted rendering service or call the API from your favourite language to get the created content.</p>

          <div class="quickstart__langc">

            <a class="quickstart__lang quickstart__lang--active" data-lang="javascript">
              <img src="https://a.storyblok.com/f/40479/9a6bef0cd2/javascript.svg" height="33">
              <span>JavaScript</span>
            </a>
            <a class="quickstart__lang" data-lang="nodejs">
              <img src="https://a.storyblok.com/f/40479/600c85c25b/node.svg" height="33">
              <span>Node.js</span>
            </a>
            <a class="quickstart__lang" data-lang="ruby">
              <img src="https://a.storyblok.com/f/40479/5b972f6821/ruby.svg" height="33">
              <span>Ruby</span>
            </a>
            <a class="quickstart__lang" data-lang="php">
              <img src="https://a.storyblok.com/f/40479/dac5c0bb11/php.svg" height="33">
              <span>PHP</span>
            </a>
            <a class="quickstart__lang" data-lang="python">
              <img src="https://a.storyblok.com/f/40479/71495561c6/python.svg" height="33">
              <span>Python</span>
            </a>
            <a class="quickstart__lang" data-lang="storyblok">
              <img src="https://a.storyblok.com/f/40479/52dd4927ef/storyblok_circle.svg" height="33">
              <span>Storyblok</span>
            </a>
          </div>



          <div class="quickstart__t quickstart__t--active" data-tab="javascript">
            <pre><code>&lt;script src="//app.storyblok.com/f/storyblok-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  storyblok.init({
    accessToken: '{{private_token}}' <span>// Your private token</span>
  }){%- raw -%}

  <span>&lt;!-- Get the content of the current page --&gt;</span>
  storyblok.get({slug: 'home', version: 'draft'}, function(data) {
    console.log(data.story)
  })

  <span>&lt;!-- Get multiple content entries from a folder called "news" --&gt;</span>
  storyblok.getAll({starts_with: 'story', version: 'draft'}, function(data) {
    console.log(data.stories)
  })
&lt;/script&gt;{% endraw %}

<span># More on <a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/add-a-headless-CMS-to-vuejs-in-5-minutes">our Blog</a></span></code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="quickstart__t" data-tab="nodejs">
            <pre><code>var StoryblokClient = require('storyblok-node-client');

var Storyblok = new StoryblokClient({
  privateToken: '{{private_token}}' <span>// Your private token</span>
});
{%- raw -%}
<span>// Get the content of the current page</span>
Storyblok
  .get('stories/home', {
    version: 'draft'
  })
  .then((response) => {
    console.log(response);
  });

<span>// Get multiple content entries from a folder called "news"</span>
Storyblok
  .get('stories', {
    starts_with: 'news'
    version: 'draft'
  })
  .then((response) => {
    console.log(response);
  });
{% endraw %}

<span># More on <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/storyblok/storyblok-node-client">Github</a></span></code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="quickstart__t" data-tab="ruby">
            <pre><code>client = new Storyblok::Client(token: '{{private_token}}') <span># Your private token</span>
{%- raw -%}
<span># Get the content of the current page</span>
p client.story('home')

<span># Get multiple content entries from a folder called "news"</span>
p client.stories({
  :starts_with => 'news'
})

<span># More on <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/storyblok/storyblok-ruby">Github</a></span>{% endraw %}</code></pre>
          </div>


          <div class="quickstart__t" data-tab="php">
            <pre><code>require 'vendor/autoload.php';

$client = new \Storyblok\Client('{{private_token}}'); <span>// Your private token</span>{%- raw -%}

<span>// Get the content of the current page</span>
$client->getStoryBySlug('home');
$data = $client->getBody();

<span>// Get multiple content entries from a folder called "news"</span>
$client->getStories(
  array(
    'starts_with' => 'news'
  )
);
$data = $client->getStoryContent();{% endraw %}

<span># More on <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/storyblok/php-client">Github</a></span></code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="quickstart__t" data-tab="python">
            <pre><code>import http.client

conn = http.client.HTTPSConnection("api.storyblok.com")

<span>// Get the content of the current page</span>
conn.request("GET", "/v1/cdn/stories/home?token={{private_token}}") <span>// Your private token</span>{%- raw -%}

res = conn.getresponse()
data = res.read()

print(data.decode("utf-8")){% endraw %}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="quickstart__t" data-tab="storyblok">
            <pre><code>{%- raw -%}<span># Get the content of the current page</span>
{{ story.content }}

<span># Get multiple content entries from a folder called "news"</span>
{% set newsitems from stories starts_with:'news', per_page: 3 %}
{% for news in newsitems.data %}
    {{ news }}
{% endfor %}

<span># Open the file views/page.liquid and try it out</span>
<span># More on <a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/docs/Rendering-Service/Theme-Documentation">theme documentation</a></span>
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <br>
          <div class="quickstart__text--center">
            <button class="btn" data-api-sdk-boilerplates-got-it data-track="interaction: api-sdk-boilerplates-got-it">I got it!</button><br>
            <button class="quickstart__button--link" data-trigger-livechat data-track="interaction: api-sdk-boilerplates-more-information">You got some questions?</button>
          </div>
          <h3>Nice to read:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/component-thinking-improves-productivity">How thinking in components can increase your productivity</a></li>
            <li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/coupled-decoupled-and-headless-content-management-systems">Coupled, Decoupled and Headless Content Management Systems</a></li>
            <li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/node-js-cms">Add a headless CMS to Node.js using Express as server.</a></li>
            <li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/add-a-headless-cms-to-laravel-in-5-minutes">Add a headless CMS to Laravel in 5 minutes</a></li>
            <li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/add-a-headless-CMS-to-vuejs-in-5-minutes">Add a headless CMS to VueJs in 5 minutes</a></li>
            <li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/add-a-headless-cms-to-python-django-in-5-minutes">Add a headless CMS to Python/Django in 5 minutes</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

      <div id="rendering-service" {% if proxy_mode %}class="quickstart--show"{% endif %}>
          <h1>Rendering Service</h1>
          <div class="step  {% if proxy_mode %} step--active {% endif %}">
            <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
            <div class="step__text">
              <h2>Fire up your local environment.</h2>
              <p>
                With the quickstart you've already got all you need to start.
                In the folder you've started to quickstart execute following commands:
              </p>
              <div class="quickstart__t quickstart__t--borderless quickstart__t--active">
                <pre><code>npm install && gulp</code></pre>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="step step--teaser-creation">
            <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
            <div class="step__text">
              <h2>Let's create your first presentation of a component</h2>
              <p>
                You've already created a component in Storyblok - so all what's left to do
                is to create a presentation for that data. So let's create a `_teaser.liquid`
                in your `/views/components/` folder.
              </p>
              <div class="quickstart__t quickstart__t--borderless quickstart__t--active">
                <pre><code>{% raw %}&lt;div class=&quot;quickstart__teaser&quot;&gt;
  &lt;!--
  The _editable attribute makes the next
  DOM-element clickable so the sidebar can
  show the right component.
  --&gt;
  {{ blok._editable }}
  &lt;div class=&quot;quickstart__inner-teaser&quot;&gt;
    &lt;svg class=&quot;icon&quot;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&quot;#icon-congrats&quot;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;h2&gt;
      &lt;!--
      You can access every attribute you
      define in the schema in the blok variable
      --&gt;
      {% if blok.headline == blank %}
        Congrats, you have inserted a teaser to the page!
      {% else %}
        {{ blok.headline }}
      {% endif %}
      &lt;/h2&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;
        Open &lt;code&gt;views/components/_teaser.liquid&lt;/code&gt; to study the code.
        &lt;!-- HINT: Try to change something and the browser window in Storyblok will automatically refresh. --&gt;
    &lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;{% endraw %}</code></pre>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          {% include story.content.component with blok: story.content, title: story.name, date: story.created_at %}

          <div class="step step--liquid-teaser">
            <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
            <div class="step__text">
              <h2>Great job!</h2>
              <p>
                Let me just summaries what you just did:
                <ul>
                  <li>Created a space</li>
                  <li>Created a story</li>
                  <li>Created a component with a schema in Storyblok</li>
                  <li>Started a local development environment on your machine</li>
                  <li>Created the presentation layer for your component</li>
                </ul>
                You can now start creating your own components with their individual schemas and their own presentation layers.
                <button class="btn" data-rendering-service-got-it data-track="interaction: rendering-service-got-it">Got it!</button>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="step">
            <div class="step__number"><span></span></div>
            <div class="step__text">
              <h2>You are ready!</h2>
              <p>
                Simply remove the <code>{% raw %}{% include 'quickstart' %}{% endraw %}</code> from your <code>/views/page.liquid</code> and you're ready to start with your own project.
                You can checkout the README.md for more information about this basic setup. Have fun!
              </p>
              <h3><button class="quickstart__button--link" data-trigger-livechat data-track="interaction: rendering-service-more-information">You need more help? Ask us right away!</button></h3>
              <h3>Nice to read:</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/component-thinking-improves-productivity">How thinking in components can increase your productivity</a></li>
                <li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/coupled-decoupled-and-headless-content-management-systems">Coupled, Decoupled and Headless Content Management Systems</a></li>
                <li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.storyblok.com/tp/how-to-get-pagespeed-100">How to optimize your website to a Pagespeed of 100</a></li>
              </ul>

            </div>
          </div>


      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

